  * Deliver best in class cyber security products & services to our customers 
  * Open to candidates from Brisbane QLD or Sydney NSW 
  * Join a collaborative close knit team 

** OUR STORY **

Fujifilm CodeBlue Australia is a Managed Services Provider, servicing a wide
range of Australia-based clients, each with diverse IT environments and
topologies. Fujifilm CodeBlue has its roots stemming back to 2003, starting
off as a Brisbane-based MSP which now supports customers remotely and locally
in all major capitals.

** THE OPPORTUNITY **

We have an exciting opportunity for a ** Cyber Security Practice Lead ** to
join our CodeBlue business.

This role will involve leading the security team to deliver best in class
cyber security products, services and consulting to CodeBlue’s Managed Service
customers. You will also be responsible for the growth of the security
practice to new and existing CodeBlue customers.

The Cyber Security Practice Lead is also responsible for the implementation
and management of internal security systems, practices, and controls to
protect company data as well as the achievement and maintenance of compliance
certifications and standards. You will also be responsible for developing and
implementing cyber security policies and strategies, educating staff on cyber
security best practice, and overseeing cyber security incidents.

At Fujifilm CodeBlue Australia, we believe our people set us apart. We are a
company totally focused on the customer experience, it is our people who bring
this vision to life by living our values and giving the best of themselves.
Driven by innovation, Fujifilm CodeBlue Australia is transforming its business
model, solutions, and customer value proposition to align and deliver on the
future business needs and requirements of Australian businesses.

** We are open to considering candidates from Brisbane QLD or Sydney NSW. **

** Key Responsibilities: **

  * Lead the CodeBlue Cyber Security Practice in all aspects 
  * Lead the cyber security team and ensure that the team is meeting the company’s cyber security objectives 
  * Lead customer meetings presenting to C-Level and management as required 
  * Understand and interpret customer needs to define and articulate solution outcomes leading to growth 
  * Develop and maintain cyber security incident response processes 
  * Stay up-to-date with the latest cyber security trends and technologies. 
  * Security Incident, Problem and Change Management 
  * Maintain company standard documentation 
  * Conduct risk assessments and vulnerability testing to identify potential security threats 
  * Internal training including Sales Enablement, Security Awareness and Service Desk 
  * Develop and implement internal Information Security strategies, policies, and procedures 
  * Acts as the “Information Security Manager” role for ISO27001 purposes 
  * Lead ISO27001 internal and external audits 
  * Own relationships with 3rd party cyber security vendors 
  * Maintains the cyber security practice budget and other financial responsibilities. 
  * Create and maintains FUJFILM CodeBlue Australia consulting products and offerings 
  * Attends and participates cyber security Industry events 

** Skills & Qualifications **

  * 5+ years' experience in Cyber Security/ Information Security with Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or related field 
  * Excellent communication and leadership skills with the ability to work under pressure 
  * Knowledge of cyber security frameworks, standards, and best practices 
  * Excellent experience with Antivirus, EDR, Firewalls, Intrusion Detection, Mail Security, Data Loss Prevention, Vulnerability Management, Penetration Testing, Patching, Operating System Hardening, Dark Web Monitoring, Application Patching and SIEM & SOAR tools. 
  * Experience in Cyber Security management and related functions such as IT Risk Management, Business Continuity Planning, Disaster Recovery, Information Management, Data Loss Prevention, Cyber Security Insurance, Information Security Awareness, etc. 
  * Excellent understanding of various Frameworks such as ISO27001, NIST, ASD Essential 8, APRA CPS 234, PCI-DSS, GDPR etc. 
  * Excellent understanding of Australia Privacy Law. 
  * Ability to manage and direct 3rd party contractors / suppliers to ensure a quality outcomes 
  * Ability to manage onshore and offshore resources 

** Desirable skills **

  * Master’s degree in Cyber/Information Security 
  * Certifications (Microsoft/ITIL/ISO/Cyber Security Related) 
  * Certifications such as CISSP or CISM 

